  "body": "With the introduction of TS 2.8, we're now able to extract types from inferences.\r\nThis allowed the creation of #1676, which now means we can infer all returned types from within sagas. Refactoring to use the above helper will reduce type fragility, and prevent types from being invalid. \r\n\r\nThis was a common problem before as `yield` returns the type of `any`, so you would have to manually type each `yield` with the return type of the function, but if that functions return type ever changed then your type would now be invalid, and the compiler would not catch it.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\n/* Before */\r\nfunction*  foo() {\r\n return 5;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction* bar() {\r\n const ret: number = yield call(foo) // have to manually type this\r\n}\r\n\r\n/* After refactor */\r\nfunction*  foo() {\r\n return '5';\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction* bar() {\r\n // this type is now invalid! \r\n // But the compiler wont throw an error since typeof yield is \"any\"\r\n const ret: number = yield call(foo)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```ts\r\n/ * With type inference #1676 * /\r\n\r\n// import our type inference helper\r\nimport { ExtSaga } from 'redux-saga/effects'\r\n\r\n/* Before */\r\n// make sure we don't type the return type of this as `SagaIterator`\r\n// it'll break type inference and return `never`\r\nfunction*  foo() { \r\n return 5;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction* bar() {\r\n // ret will be typeof 'number'\r\n const ret: ExtSaga<typeof foo> = yield call(foo) // type is now automatically extracted\r\n}\r\n\r\n/* After refactor */\r\nfunction*  foo() {\r\n return '5';\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction* bar() {\r\n // ret will be typeof 'string'\r\n const ret: ExtSaga<typeof foo> =  yield call(foo) // this type is still valid\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
